The course presents an overview of the main notions of phonetics, phonemes and their formation.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) to improve the students' pronunciation; 2) to give an overview of the main notions of phonetics; 3) to explain the formation of phonemes in the Estonian language and compare it with the phoneme formation in the Russian language; 4) to explain the essence of the accent, the reasons for its occurrence and possible disappearance.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) an understanding of basic phonetic concepts and phenomena and how these are related together, as well as the articulation of Estonian language sounds; 2) is able to compare it to the articulation of sounds in the Russian language; 3) has a firm grasp of the nature of accent and its causes and is able to speak without phonetic accent; 4) the student can teach pronunciation of the Estonian language and eliminate possible phonetic accent.
